- Review insurance coverage to make sure it is enough to replace your property

Survive During
- Evacuate immediately
- If trapped call 9 1 1 give your location
- Listen to emergency broadcasts
- If you're not asked to leave but smoky conditions exist, stay inside in a safe location or go to a community building where smoke levels are lowerl

After -

- Keep listening to authorities to find out when you can return, and whether water is safe to drink.
- Avoid hot ash, charred trees, smoldering debris and live embers. The ground may contain heat pockets that can burn you or spark another fire. Consider pets and young children in this regard
- Send text msg or send social media to let friends and family know you're safe. Phone systems are often busy following a disaster, and should be used for emergency on
- Document property damage with photographs, conduct an inventory and contact your insurance company
